<span class="displaytext"><b></b><p>(candidate full)<br/>cbs' "early show"<br/>april 25, 2008 </p><p>cbs' maggie rodriguez: "senator, you're connecting with people who are facing two of the biggest issues in this election and in our country right now, the economy and health care. if you're elected president, where would your immediate focus be?" <b></b></p><p>(candidate full): "my immediate purpose would be to get our economy going again. and to make sure that families make the decisions in health care in america and not the big government, as senator (candidate last) and senator (candidate last) want to do. as far as the economy is concerned, don't raise taxes the way senator (candidate last) wants to do on capital gains. if you want to raise taxes, then don't vote for me." <b><i></i></b></p><p> <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yd6lcppmss4"><b><i><u> watch</u></i></b> </a><b><i>(candidate full) on cbs' "early show" </i></b></p></span>



